I was already aware that the use of Flash under Linux emulation is
accompanied by difficulties. However, I find that if I attempt to open
a Flash file using linux-firefox (which I'm using right now) it
immediately crashes, with the following output:

$ linux-firefox
Segmentation fault
$ Warning: Cannot convert string &quot;-adobe-helvetica-medium-r-*-12-*&quot; to
type FontStruct
Warning: Cannot convert string &quot;-adobe-helvetica-bold-r-*-12-*&quot; to
type FontStruct

Is there any way to mitigate such problems? Or do we just have to hope
that Adobe will provide a native FreeBSD application?
</POST>
