&quot;Mitigate&quot; is a good word; there are a some things I do that make
such problems less annoying and less common, but there is nothing
that would count as a solution.  To start with, I install the
Flashblock extension, so that I don't get annoyed by Flash
displays unless I specifically want them (some bits of Flash
reliably cause problems, others reliably do not).  Also, different
versions of Flash give me different results on specific bits of
Flash code.

Incidentally, my experiences with Flash are not rock-solid under
Linux either, so waiting for Adobe to solve the problem for us
doe not look like a good option.
